Package tree

Interface ITree<TREETYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    TREETYPE - The typeparameter defines the type of the ITree and its ITreeNodes.
    All Superinterfaces:
    IDeepCopy, ISearchableByFilter<ITreeNode<TREETYPE>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GenericTree, ProductTree
    public interface ITree<TREETYPE>
extends IDeepCopy, ISearchableByFilter<ITreeNode<TREETYPE>>
    This interface specifies the behavior of a simple tree-structure of ITreeNodes. It enables handling of the root ITreeNode. In addition, methods for searching ITreeNodes and generating a string representation of the ITree are provided.

    The interface extends the IDeepCopy interface and thus copies of ITrees can be created.

    The interface extends the ISearchableByFilter interface. This allows to filter elements of the ITree by an ISearchFilter. The result is returned as a Collection of ITreeNodes.

    Author:
    OOP

      • removeNode

        boolean removeNode​(ITreeNode<TREETYPE> removeNode)
        This method traverses the ITree and removes the passed ITreeNode from it. If a matching ITreeNode is found in the ITree, the ITreeNode is removed. In this case the ITreeNode and all its children are removed from the ITree.
        Parameters:
        removeNode - The node to be removed from the ITree.
        Returns:
        TRUE if an ITreeNode was removed, FALSE otherwise.

      • deepCopy

        ITree<TREETYPE> deepCopy()
        Description copied from interface: IDeepCopy
        Creates and returns a copy of this object. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression: 
         x.deepCopy() != x
        will be true, and that the expression: 
         x.deepCopy().getClass() == x.getClass()
        will be true, but these are not absolute requirements. While it is typically the case that: 
         x.deepCopy().equals(x)
        will be true, this is not an absolute requirement.
